@node about " Multi-Menus v1.2 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS""
@prev main
@{"°°" link grems}
   ___  _              _
  / _ \| |__  ___ _  _| |_
 |  _  | '_ \/ _ \ || |  _|
 |_| |_|_.__/\___/\_,_|\__|                          @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Multi-Menus allows up to 5 styles (or sets) of different menus on the BBS
 instead of the same menus all the time, at the user's choice.

 This is a tiny update from Version 1.0 of Multi_Menus ('97).

@endnode
@node run " Multi-Menus v1.2 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS""
@{"°°" link grems}
  ___         _        _ _
 |_ _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  | || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |___|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                          @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly (if you already haven't) create a new directory called "gremlins"
 in your doors directory. Assign "gremlins" to your doors path in the user
 startup sequence, eg: "assign gremlins: doors:gremlins" assuming you have
 the doors path assigned also, which is normal.

 Move the "Multi-Menus" directory into the "gremlins" dir and run the door
 via a menu option (..or via Introdoor.text sequence). Upon running Multi-
 Menus, you can have up to 5 different  style menu options (1 to 5) and an
 option for [i]nfo.

 You must assign Menus, eg: "assign menus: bbs:menus/". All your paths for
 each menu to display in the MAXs menu editor must start with "Menus:" and
 most SysOp's should already have done, if not, you're behind. ;)

 Eg: menus:games-menu.text

 Option 1 in Multi-Menus is always the default menus that reside in menus:
 and for each other option for other style menus, they must reside in each
 seperate directory, for example, Option 2 menus reside in "menus:menus2/"
 and Option 3 menus  in "menus:menus3/" and so on.  So for each style menu
 you must create a new directory in the main menus path, eg: "menus2", etc
 and only create directories if you need too.  If a selection is not made,
 then Multi-Menus always assigns the default menus.

 To ensure the default menus are assigned each time a user logs off or on,
 put the following (..which is optional) in your logoff.script.

 Eg: "assign menus: bbs:menus/"

 I think you all get the general  idea of how Multi-Menus works, etc and I
 hope you don't have too many probs, if so then @{"contact" link call} me!

@endnode
